---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { slug: 'openai-codex-agent' } },
    { params: { slug: 'ai-agent-market-size' } },
    { params: { slug: 'devin-first-ai-engineer' } },
    { params: { slug: 'multi-agent-systems' } },
    { params: { slug: 'agent-income-generation' } },
    { params: { slug: 'google-announced-agent-payments-protocol-ap2' } },
  ];
}

const { slug } = Astro.params;

const posts = {
  'openai-codex-agent': {
    titleZh: 'OpenAI Codex：AI 软件智能体的崛起',
    titleEn: 'OpenAI Codex: The Rise of AI Software Agents',
    date: '2026-02-08',
    contentZh: `
      <p>OpenAI 发布了 Codex，一款能够自主编写、调试和部署代码的突破性 AI 智能体。这代表着 AI 智能体能够执行复杂软件工程任务的重大里程碑。</p>
      
      <p>主要功能包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>自主代码生成和调试</li>
        <li>与开发环境集成</li>
        <li>能够处理多个文件和复杂代码库</li>
        <li>与人类开发者实时协作</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>对智能体经济的影响是深远的。随着这些工具变得越来越强大，我们可能会看到软件开发方式的转变，AI 智能体将处理越来越复杂的任务。</p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>OpenAI has unveiled Codex, a groundbreaking AI agent capable of autonomously writing, debugging, and deploying code. This represents a major milestone in the development of AI agents that can perform complex software engineering tasks.</p>
      
      <p>Key features include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Autonomous code generation and debugging</li>
        <li>Integration with development environments</li>
        <li>Ability to handle multiple files and complex codebases</li>
        <li>Real-time collaboration with human developers</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>The implications for the agent economy are significant. As these tools become more capable, we may see a shift in how software is developed, with AI agents handling increasingly complex tasks.</p>
    `,
    tags: ['OpenAI', 'Codex', 'AI Agents', 'Development'],
    source: 'Hacker News'
  },
  'ai-agent-market-size': {
    titleZh: 'AI 智能体市场：2030 年将达到 2160 亿美元',
    titleEn: 'The AI Agent Market: $216 Billion by 2030',
    date: '2026-02-07',
    contentZh: `
      <p>根据最新市场研究，自主 AI 智能体市场预计到 2030 年将达到 2160 亿美元，复合年增长率（CAGR）超过 40%。</p>
      
      <p>增长驱动力包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>企业采用客户服务和客户支持</li>
        <li>个人生产力领域的消费者应用</li>
        <li>与现有软件平台的集成</li>
        <li>大型语言模型的进步</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>这个市场规模表明，AI 智能体正在从实验性技术转变为主流商业工具。</p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>According to recent market research, the autonomous AI agent market is projected to reach $216 billion by 2030, representing a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of over 40%.</p>
      
      <p>The growth is driven by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Enterprise adoption for customer service and support</li>
        <li>Consumer applications in personal productivity</li>
        <li>Integration with existing software platforms</li>
        <li>Advancements in large language models</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>This market size indicates that AI agents are moving from experimental technology to mainstream business tools.</p>
    `,
    tags: ['Market Research', 'AI Economy', 'Business'],
    source: 'Industry Report'
  },
  'devin-first-ai-engineer': {
    titleZh: 'Devin：首个完全自主的 AI 软件工程师',
    titleEn: 'Devin: The First Fully Autonomous AI Software Engineer',
    date: '2026-02-06',
    contentZh: `
      <p>Cognition Labs 推出了 Devin，一个能够独立规划、编码、调试和部署软件应用程序的 AI 系统。与编码助手不同，Devin 可以从头到尾完成整个项目。</p>
      
      <p>Devin 的能力包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>将复杂项目分解为可管理的步骤</li>
        <li>独立编写和测试代码</li>
        <li>调试和修复错误</li>
        <li>部署到生产环境</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>这代表着向真正自主的软件开发智能体迈出了重要一步。</p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>Cognition Labs has introduced Devin, an AI system that can independently plan, code, debug, and deploy software applications. Unlike coding assistants, Devin can work on entire projects from start to finish.</p>
      
      <p>Devin's capabilities include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Breaking down complex projects into manageable steps</li>
        <li>Writing and testing code independently</li>
        <li>Debugging and fixing errors</li>
        <li>Deploying to production environments</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>This represents a significant step toward truly autonomous software development agents.</p>
    `,
    tags: ['Devin', 'AI Engineering', 'Autonomous AI'],
    source: 'TechCrunch'
  },
  'multi-agent-systems': {
    titleZh: '多智能体系统：下一个前沿',
    titleEn: 'Multi-Agent Systems: The Next Frontier',
    date: '2026-02-05',
    contentZh: `
      <p>多智能体系统的研究正在显示出有希望的结果，多个 AI 智能体协作解决单个智能体无法独自处理的问题。</p>
      
      <p>主要进展包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>智能体专业化和角色分配</li>
        <li>智能体间通信协议</li>
        <li>协作问题解决</li>
        <li>智能体交互中的涌现行为</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>这些系统可以实现在业务流程和科学研究中更复杂的自动化。</p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>Research in multi-agent systems is showing promising results, where multiple AI agents collaborate to solve problems that single agents cannot handle alone.</p>
      
      <p>Key developments include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Agent specialization and role assignment</li>
        <li>Inter-agent communication protocols</li>
        <li>Collaborative problem solving</li>
        <li>Emergent behaviors from agent interactions</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>These systems could enable more complex automation in business processes and scientific research.</p>
    `,
    tags: ['Multi-Agent', 'Research', 'AI Systems'],
    source: 'Hacker News'
  },
  'agent-income-generation': {
    titleZh: 'AI 智能体能产生真实收入吗？',
    titleEn: 'Can AI Agents Generate Real Income?',
    date: '2026-02-04',
    contentZh: `
      <p>随着 AI 智能体变得越来越强大，一个新问题出现了：它们能否为其所有者创造实际的经济价值和收入？</p>
      
      <p>新兴模式包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>AI 智能体提供自由职业服务</li>
        <li>自动化内容创作和变现</li>
        <li>交易和金融管理机器人</li>
        <li>客户服务和客户支持自动化</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>虽然还处于早期阶段，但一些企业家已经开始报告从 AI 智能体运营中获得的收入。</p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>As AI agents become more capable, a new question emerges: Can they generate actual economic value and income for their owners?</p>
      
      <p>Emerging models include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>AI agents providing freelance services</li>
        <li>Automated content creation and monetization</li>
        <li>Trading and financial management bots</li>
        <li>Customer service and support automation</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>While still early, some entrepreneurs are already reporting income from AI agent operations.</p>
    `,
    tags: ['Economics', 'AI Business', 'Future of Work'],
    source: 'Blog Analysis'
  },
  'google-announced-agent-payments-protocol-ap2': {
    titleZh: 'Google 发布 Agent Payments Protocol (AP2)',
    titleEn: 'Google Announced Agent Payments Protocol (AP2)',
    date: '2025-09-16',
    contentZh: `
      <p>Google 发布了 Agent Payments Protocol (AP2)，这是一个建立在 A2A (Agent to Agent Protocol) 之上的开放协议。AP2 由 Google 与领先的支付和技术公司共同开发，旨在安全地实现 AI 智能体之间的支付交易。</p>
      
      <p>主要特点包括：</p>
      <ul>
        <li>基于 A2A 协议构建的开放标准</li>
        <li>支持 AI 智能体之间的安全支付</li>
        <li>与 Google Cloud 生态系统深度集成</li>
        <li>推动智能体经济的商业化发展</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>这标志着 AI 智能体从实验走向实际商业应用的重要一步，为智能体经济的基础设施建设提供了关键支撑。</p>
      
      <p>阅读完整文章：<a href="https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol">https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol</a></p>
    `,
    contentEn: `
      <p>Google has announced the Agent Payments Protocol (AP2), an open protocol that builds on A2A (Agent to Agent Protocol). AP2 was developed by Google with leading payments and technology companies to securely enable payment transactions between AI agents.</p>
      
      <p>Key features include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Open standard built on A2A protocol</li>
        <li>Supports secure payments between AI agents</li>
        <li>Deep integration with Google Cloud ecosystem</li>
        <li>Advances the commercialization of the agent economy</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p>This marks an important step in AI agents moving from experimentation to actual commercial applications, providing critical infrastructure support for the agent economy.</p>
      
      <p>Read the full article at <a href="https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol">https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/ai-machine-learning/announcing-agents-to-payments-ap2-protocol</a></p>
    `,
    tags: ['Google', 'AP2', 'Payments', 'AI Economy'],
    source: 'Google Cloud Blog'
  }
};

const post = posts[slug];
---

<Layout>
  <article class="article-content">
    <div class="lang-content lang-zh active">
      <h1>{post.titleZh}</h1>
    </div>
    <div class="lang-content lang-en">
      <h1>{post.titleEn}</h1>
    </div>
    <time>{post.date} · Source: {post.source}</time>
    
    <div class="lang-content lang-zh active" set:html={post.contentZh} />
    <div class="lang-content lang-en" set:html={post.contentEn} />
    
    <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
      <div class="tags">
        {post.tags.map(tag => (
          <span>{tag}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
  
  <a href="/" class="back-link" data-zh="← 全部文章" data-en="← All articles">← All articles</a>
</Layout>
